  "summary": "onboardconnect-agent posts environment data to attacker-controlled Cloudflare Worker at install time",
  "details": "The package's dist/setup.js performs an HTTPS POST to https://oc-worker-tenant-api.wpolanco.workers.dev carrying values read from process.env. The destination is a personal Cloudflare Worker (wpolanco.workers.dev) that does not match any publisher identity for an 'onboardconnect-agent' tool. dist/server.js contains additional hardcoded POST endpoints and a 'ping' invocation, and dist/crypto.js / dist/store.js use Buffer.from(..., 'base64') decoding patterns consistent with packed payloads. The combination of a hardcoded non-publisher exfiltration endpoint receiving environment variables plus base64-decoded payload handling in adjacent modules is the canonical install/setup-time credential exfiltration shape.",
